open-cobol
------------------------------------------
OpenCOBOL is a free and open-source COBOL compiler. cobc translates COBOL to
executable using intermediate C sources, providing full access to nearly all C
libraries.

Runtime requirements:
  bash-4.3.39-2
  cygwin-2.0.3-1
  cygwin-devel-2.0.3-1
  libcob-devel-2.0-1bl2
  libcob4-2.0-1bl2
  libdb-devel-5.3.21-1
  libdb5.3-5.3.21-1
  libgmp-devel-6.0.0a-2
  libgmp10-6.0.0a-2
  libncurses-devel-5.9-20150516-1
  libncursesw10-5.9-20150516-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-9-1
  binutils-2.25-2
  bison-3.0.4-1
  cygport-0.20.0-1
  gcc-core-4.9.2-3
  libtool-2.4.6-1
  make-4.1-1

Canonical website:
  http://www.opencobol.org/

Canonical download:
  mirror://sourceforge/open-cobol/open-cobol-2.0-feb2012.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack open-cobol-2.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./open-cobol-2.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/open-cobol-2.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/open-cobol-2.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libcob4-2.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libcob-devel-2.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(open-cobol)
  /usr/bin/cobc.exe
